The paper deals with the Proper Interval Completion problem, which is a graph problem related to interval graphs. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper involves parameterized complexity, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
